data.current_description:
An OpenID Connect Session Management iframe to facilitate e.g. single sign-on or remote logouts.

The iframe implements the OIDC postMessage-based [change notification protocol](http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-session-1_0.html#ChangeNotification) via which a client can receive notifications about session state changes.
data.description_suggestion: Returns an OpenID Connect Session Management iframe for the specified client. This iframe enables session state monitoring and facilitates operations such as single sign-on (SSO) and remote logouts. The iframe implements the OIDC postMessage-based change notification protocol, allowing the client to receive real-time notifications about session state changes. Embed the returned iframe in your application to maintain session awareness across multiple tabs/windows. Requires the client_id parameter.
data.reasoning: Original summary 'Include a session iframe' is vague and doesn't clarify that this is a retrieval operation. Description lacks clarity about the client_id parameter requirement and what the caller should do with the returned iframe. data.current_description:
Start a session with Authentiq Connect to authenticate a user.

```
GET https://connect.authentiq.io/authorize?client_id=<your-client-id>&response_type=code+id_token&scope=openid+email&redirect_uri=<your-redirect-uri>&state=0123456789
```

This endpoint also supports the POST method.
data.description_suggestion: Initiates an OAuth 2.0 authorization request to authenticate an end-user. Accepts 11 parameters including client_id, response_type, scope, redirect_uri, and state. Supports both GET and POST methods. On successful authentication, redirects to the specified redirect_uri with authorization code and/or ID token in the response. Requires valid client registration and matching redirect_uri. State parameter is recommended for CSRF protection.

data.description_suggestion: Exchanges an authorization code for ID Token and/or Access Token as part of the OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow. Returns a Token object containing access_token, id_token, token_type, and expires_in. Required for completing the authentication flow after user authorization.
